%20John%20Boland%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20vice%20chairman%20at%20the%20real%20estate%20services%20firm%20Newmark.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20glad%20I'm%2067%20years%20old%20and%20my%20career%20is%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoland%20said%20that%20he%20personally%20supported%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20cost%20cutting%2C%20but%20also%20acknowledged%20the%20way%20it's%20%26quot%3Breally%20spooking%20people%20in%20the%20marketplace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20nonprofit%20groups%20have%20told%20him%20they%20may%20need%20%26quot%3Ba%20third%20of%20the%20space%20or%20maybe%20nothing%20at%20all%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20lose%20government%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20office%20market%20is%20coming%20off%20of%20an%20upswing.%20Eight%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20space%20was%20leased%20in%202024%2C%20the%20highest%20total%20in%20three%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20real%20estate%20services%20and%20brokerage%20company%20CBRE.%20Vacancy%20declined%20slightly%2C%20to%2022.5%25%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20leasing%20was%20the%20largest%20driver%20of%20activity%2C%20and%20nonprofits%20were%20the%20third%20largest%20behind%20law%20firms%2C%20according%20to%20CBRE.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f9690a6-aaa2-4618-94a5-e18ce07641d8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20federal%20downsizing%20could%20now%20accelerate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20grew%20steadily%20in%20the%20capital%20region%2C%20topping%20at%20roughly%2057.5%20million%20square%20feet%20in%202011%2C%20according%20to%20Cushman%20%26amp%3B%20Wakefield.%20Since%20then%2C%20efforts%20under%20both%20Republican%20and%20Democratic%20administrations%20have%20been%20ongoing%20for%20years%20to%20reduce%20that%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20have%20seen%20over%20the%20last%2015%20years%20is%20a%20shedding%20of%20real%20estate%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20federal%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Darian%20LeBlanc%2C%20an%20executive%20vice%20chairman%20at%20Cushman%20%26amp%3B%20Wakefield%20who%20manages%20its%20government%20services%20group.%20LeBlanc%20said%20that%20the%20federal%20portfolio%20is%20now%20around%2043.5%20million%20square%20feet%20in%20size%20in%20the%20DC%20region%20%E2%80%94%20a%2024%25%20reduction%20from%20the%20peak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20federal%20workers%20embraced%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20have%20continued%20to%20work%20remotely.%20LeBlanc%20said%20that%20currently%2C%20an%20average%20of%20about%20only%2020%25%20of%20workers%20were%20in%20the%20office%20on%20any%20given%20day%20across%20most%20federal%20agencies.%20The%20new%20administration%20has%20roiled%20federal%20office%20employees%20by%20ordering%20them%20to%20return%20to%20the%20office%20full%20time%20while%20offering%20those%20who%20resign%20payment%20through%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20are%20most%20welcome%20to%20stay%20at%20home%20and%20relax%20or%20to%20travel%20to%20your%20dream%20destination%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opm.gov%2Ffork%2Ffaq%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrequently%20asked%20questions%20page%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20US%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management%20stated%2C%20describing%20the%20deferred%20resignation%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fpresidential-actions%2F2025%2F01%2Flimiting-lame-duck-collective-bargaining-agreements-that-improperly-attempt-to-constrain-the-new-president%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%20he%20will%20seek%20to%20tear%20up%20labor%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20struck%20between%20labor%20unions%20that%20represent%20the%20federal%20workforce%20and%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20Some%20of%20those%20unions%20have%20negotiated%20employment%20agreements%20that%20permit%20employees%20to%20work%20remotely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnions%20have%20reacted%20angrily%20to%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%2C%20including%20the%20paid%20resignation%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20maneuver%20is%20intended%20to%20panic%20civil%20servants%20into%20accepting%20what%20seems%20like%20a%20sweet%20deal%20but%20is%20probably%20a%20scam%2C%26quot%3B%20Randy%20Erwin%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Federal%20Employees%2C%20a%20union%20that%20represents%20110%2C000%20government%20workers%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222c5e8653-76fa-4439-9336-c1374563108e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENonprofits%20could%20cut%20space%20amid%20cuts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%20sweeping%20Trump's%20efforts%20to%20change%20the%20federal%20government's%20workforce%20and%20office%20portfolio%20may%20be%2C%20experts%20say%20the%20impacts%20will%20take%20years%20to%20be%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20federal%20government%20never%20does%20anything%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20LeBlanc%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20never%20have%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20reasonable%20to%20think%20that%20this%20is%20something%20they%20will%20act%20immediately%20upon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonprofits%2C%20however%2C%20which%20depend%20heavily%20on%20federal%20financial%20support%20could%20be%20more%20quickly%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20more%20than%2029%2C000%20nonprofits%20that%20spend%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year%20or%20more%20on%20their%20office%20occupancy%20and%20receive%20government%20assistance%2C%20according%20to%20Open%20Impact%20Real%20Estate%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20services%20and%20advisory%20firm%20that%20specializes%20in%20nonprofit%20work.%20A%20third%20of%20them%20rely%20on%20federal%20dollars%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20their%20budgets%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drastic%20cuts%20being%20pursued%20by%20the%20new%20administration%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20catastrophic%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20world%2C%20Stephen%20Powers%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Open%20Impact%2C%20said.%20He%20noted%20that%20the%20impact%20would%20be%20disproportionately%20felt%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20and%20New%20York%20City%2C%20where%20the%20nonprofit%20sector%20is%20clustered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BClients%20of%20mine%20are%20not%20signing%20leases%2C%26quot%3B%20Powers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonprofit%20groups%20occupy%20about%207%25%20of%20the%20total%20office%20space%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20metropolitan%20region%2C%20and%2012%25%20in%20the%20city%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e34c50db-259a-4ff1-bca0-e9df2bfca0b9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20landlords%20remain%20optimistic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20is%20as%20gloomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHilary%20Goldfarb%2C%20a%20senior%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20development%20company%20Rockefeller%20Group%20who%20leads%20its%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20operations%2C%20pointed%20to%20a%20flurry%20of%20law%20firm%20and%20lobbying%20leasing%20in%20the%20city%20that%20she%20believes%20will%20be%20robust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20firms%2C%20which%20often%20have%20in-house%20lobbying%20operations%20in%20the%20region%2C%20accounted%20for%2020%25%20of%20the%20office%20space%20taken%20in%20the%20city%20last%20year%2C%20according%20to%20CBRE%2C%20making%20it%20the%20second-biggest%20tenant%20group%20by%20leasing%20activity%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERockefeller%20Group%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20building%20a%20roughly%20400%2C000-square-foot%20office%20building%20at%20600%20Fifth%20St.%2C%20with%20a%20completion%20scheduled%20for%20the%20summer%20of%202026.%20It%20preleased%20about%20half%20of%20the%20project's%20space%20to%20the%20law%20firm%20Crowell%20%26amp%3B%20Moring%20in%202023%20and%20is%20marketing%20the%20remainder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20view%20is%20one%20of%20optimism%2C%20not%20uncertainty%20or%20lack%20of%20clari