80%94%20if%20not%20feeding%20on%20%E2%80%94%20the%20trend%20that%20we're%20seeing%20more%20and%20more%20MDs%20looking%20for%20nonclinical%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-doctor-who-battled-covid-19-warns-of-overwhelmed-hospitals-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECOVID-19%20pandemic%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20left%20doctors%20overworked%2C%20underappreciated%2C%20and%20constantly%20exposed%20to%20new%20workplace%20hazards.%20The%20World%20Health%20Organization%20estimated%20that%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20health%20workers%20died%20globally%20in%202020%20and%202021.%20A%20study%20published%20in%20the%20JAMA%20Health%20Forum%20found%20the%20proportion%20of%20clinicians%20looking%20to%20leave%20their%20roles%20jumped%20from%2030%25%20in%202019%20to%20more%20than%2040%25%20in%202021.%20A%202022%20survey%20from%20the%20consulting%20firm%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20found%20that%20one%20in%20four%20clinicians%20were%20considering%20a%20career%20switch%2C%20many%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnurses-doctors-face-burnout-due-to-health-care-system-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eburnout%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Today's%20physicians%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bpushed%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Myers%2C%20%26quot%3Bto%20think%20about%20different%20options.%26quot%3B%20And%20one%20of%20the%20most%20compelling%20options%20is%20the%20booming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdigital-health-startups-mega-deals-raise-funding-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edigital%20health%20industry%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20%241.5%20trillion%20by%202032%2C%20growing%20by%20nearly%2019%25%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20doctors%2C%20the%20sense%20they%20have%20a%20calling%20to%20medicine%20makes%20the%20near-decade%20of%20school%2C%20often%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20debt%2C%20and%20grueling%20on-call%20hours%20worth%20it.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20gets%20into%20medicine%20to%20be%20an%20administrator%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr.%20Guy%20Maytal.%20But%20the%20starkly%20inequitable%20healthcare%20system%20at%20times%20left%20him%20feeling%20helpless.%20He%20says%20patients%20have%20told%20him%20they%20could%20afford%20medication%20or%20food%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20both.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20decided%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20could%20grumble%20on%20the%20sidelines%20or%20roll%20up%20my%20sleeves%20and%20do%20something%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%20In%202023%2C%20after%20nearly%20two%20decades%20of%20practicing%20psychiatry%20at%20Massachusetts%20General%20Hospital%20and%20then%20Weill%20Cornell%20Medicine%20in%20New%20York%2C%20Maytal%20joined%20Forge%20Health%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20offers%20mental%20health%20and%20substance%20use%20treatments%20in-person%20and%20via%20telehealth.%20He%20says%20he%20now%20feels%20he%20has%20a%20much%20broader%20impact%20and%20ability%20to%20influence%20change%20at%20a%20quicker%20pace%20than%20he%20could%20when%20he%20was%20seeing%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CMO%20role%20has%20expanded%20and%20evolved%20as%20the%20health%20tech%20industry%20has%20come%20under%20more%20scrutiny.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheranos-founder-ceo-elizabeth-holmes-life-story-bio-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETheranos%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20cautionary%20tale%20of%20the%20biotech%20world%2C%20had%20a%20board%20that%20lacked%20medical%20expertise.%20A%20dermatologist%20who%20had%20treated%20Theranos'%20president%2C%20Ramesh%20%26quot%3BSunny%26quot%3B%20Balwani%2C%20was%20hired%20as%20the%20company's%20lab%20director%20in%202014.%20He%20had%20no%20board%20certification%20related%20to%20pathology%20or%20laboratory%20science.%20Only%20after%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20exposed%20flaws%20in%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20company's%20blood-testing%20method%20in%202015%20did%20the%20company%20create%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheranos-adds-members-to-scientific-and-medical-advisory-board-2016-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emedical%20and%20scientific%20advisory%20board%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20company%20that%20wants%20to%20build%20trust%2C%20and%20avoid%20becoming%20another%20Theranos%2C%20%26quot%3Bmight%20certainly%20consider%20hiring%20a%20CMO%20to%20give%20a%20trusted%20voice%20to%20their%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20Myers%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20trust%20their%20doctors%20to%20have%20their%20best%20interest%20in%20mind%26quot%3B%20over%20a%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20quantify%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20CMO.%20Major%20medical%20associations%20in%20the%20US%20told%20me%20they%20don't%20have%20data%20on%20the%20number%20of%20people%20working%20in%20these%20positions.%20But%20Data%20from%20ZipRecruiter%20found%20the%20number%20of%20job%20postings%20seeking%20chief%20medical%20officers%20jumped%20from%20767%20in%202019%20to%20more%20than%205%2C000%20in%202021.%20In%202024%2C%20there%20were%202%2C154%20such%20job%20posts.%20In%202022%2C%20Emory%20University%20began%20offering%20a%20first-of-its-kind%20executive%20program%20to%20train%20chief%20medical%20officers%20for%20leadership%20positions%20in%20healthcare.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Jonathan%20Jaffery%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20health%20care%20affairs%20at%20the%20Association%20of%20American%20Medical%20Colleges%2C%20says%20that%20people%20rarely%20leave%20medical%20school%20to%20directly%20take%20on%20administrative%20work%20but%20slowly%20add%20those%20tasks%20throughout%20their%20career%20before%20making%20the%20switch.%20For%20the%20most%20part%2C%20doctors%20aren't%20jumping%20from%20the%20ER%20to%20startups%3B%20the%20decision%20to%20use%20their%20medical%20expertise%20for%20work%20other%20than%20seeing%20patients%20happens%20gradually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20still%20relatively%20new%2C%20the%20CMO%20remains%20an%20amorphous%20role%2C%20bending%20to%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20an%20app%20and%20its%20users%20or%20a%20company's%20workforce.%20They%20might%20work%20on%20product%20development%2C%20research%20consumer%20safety%2C%20or%20analyze%20employee%20benefits%20and%20policies.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20they're%20often%20balancing%20the%20business%20objectives%20of%20a%20startup%20with%20the%20Hippocratic%20oath%20they've%20taken%20to%20support%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-salesforce-chief-medical-officer-got-her-job-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESalesforce%20added%20a%20CMO%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019%2C%20whose%20role%20focused%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-wellbeing-programs-help-companies-perform-better-and-manage-cost-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemployee%20well-being%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Google%20hired%20its%20first%20chief%20health%20officer%20in%202019.%20These%20are%20jobs%20that%20don't%20always%20focus%20on%20patients%20or%20a%20product%3B%20they%20might%20involve%20deciding%20which%20benefits%20companies%20offer%20to%20their%20employees%20or%20implementing%20ways%20to%20protect%20employees'%20health.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20are%20trying%20to%20take%20ownership%20more%20and%20more%20of%20employee%20health%20and%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Anna%20Tavis%2C%20a%20clinical%20professor%20of%20human%20capital%20management%20at%20New%20York%20University.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eever-growing%20healthcare%20costs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20could%20be%20more%20demand%20for%20health%20tech%20and%20healthcare%20coaching%20as%20part%20of%20employee%20benefits%20packages%20or%20for%20medical%20experts%20who%20can%20advise%20companies%20on%20the%20best%20tech%20tools%20to%20use%20for%20preventive%20care%20and%20mental%20health%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Joshua%20Sclar%20serves%20as%20the%20chief%20clinical%20and%20public%20health%20advisor%20at%20Uber%20Health%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20ride-hailing%20giant%20that%20transports%20people%20to%20doctor's%20appointments%20and%20delivers%20medicine%20or%20groceries.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20a%20physician%2C%20I%20know%20what%20happens%20when%20that%20care%20is%20missed%2C%26quot%3B%20not%20just%20to%20a%20patient%2C%20but%20to%20the%20healthcare%20system%20as%20whole%2C%20Sclar%20says%20of%20his%20role%20in%20translating%20healthcare%20needs%20to%20the%20transportation%20company.%20Sclar%20previously%20worked%20in%20three%20other%20CMO%20roles%20and%20was%20the%20first%20hired%20at%20each.%20At%20Uber%20Health%2C%20Sclar%20says%20he%20was%20surprised%20to%20learn%20how%20complex%20the%20technology%20behind%20the%20app%20was%2C%20given%20how%20seamlessly%20ride-hailing%20apps%20appear%20to%20consumers.%20Other%20CMOs%20agree%20that%20there's%20a%20learning%20curve%20when%20moving%20from%20the%20medical%20world%20to%20the%20business%20world.%20Maytal%20says%20his%20new%20role%20has%20him%20translating%20medical%20jargon%20and%20learning%20business%20jargon.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20my%20first%20time%20in%20my%20professional%20life%20where%20my%20boss%20wasn't%20a%20doctor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Nikole%20Benders-Hadi%2C%20the%20chief%20medical%20officer%20at%20the%20online%20therapy%20company%20TalkSpace%20%E2%80%94%20and%20formerly%20the%20chief%20of%20psychiatry%20at%20a%20psychiatric%20center%20%E2%80%94%20has%20had%20similar%20experiences.%20As%20her%20role%20as%20CMO%20has%20shifted%2C%20%26quot%3Boftentimes%2C%20it%20was%20me%20sitting%20in%20the%20room%20as%20the%20only%20mental%20health%20clinician%20thinking%20really%20critically%20about%20how%20I%20communicate%20my%20unique%20perspective%20in%20this%20room%20with%20all%20these%20business%20folks%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere%20can%20be%20really%20different%20end%20goals%20when%20you're%20talking%20about%20business%20objectives%20versus%20healthcare%20objectives.%26quot%3B%20Sclar%20believes%20many%20healthcare%20companies%20could%20benefit%20from%20bringing%20physicians%20into%20leadership%20roles.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThose%20on%20the%20business%20side%20might%20know%20how%20to%20scale%20a%20company%2C%20but%20physicians%20give%20insight%20into%20whether%20the%20product%20will%20%26quot%3Btranslate%20to%20the%20impact%20on%20health%20that%20we%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20challenges%2C%20for%20physicians%20accustomed%20to%20sleeping%20next%20to%20phones%20while%20on%20call%20and%20spending%20hours%20fighting%20insurance%20companies%20after%20seeing%20sick%20patients%2C%20moving%20from%20the%20ER%20to%20the%20C-suite%20can%20take%20less%20of%20an%20emotional%20toll.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20busy%2C%20they're%20hectic%2C%20they%20seem%20very%20stressful%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20life%20and%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaffery%20says%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20often%20arise%20in%20administrative%20positions.%20The%20average%20salary%20for%20a%20CMO%20across%20the%20US%20is%20about%20%24275%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20ZipRecruiter%20data%20%E2%80%94%20comparable%20with%20the%20average%20doctor's%20salary%2C%20but%20with%20more%20humane%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20in%20CMOs%20comes%20as%20America%20faces%20a%20dire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-hospital-wait-times-are-bad-physician-shortage-low-pay-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eshortage%20of%20physicians%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Association%20of%20American%20Medical%20Colleges%20said%20the%20US%20is%20on%20track%20to%20be%20short%2086%2C000%20physicians%20by%202036%2C%20as%20a%20large%20number%20of%20doctors%20near%20retirement%20age%20and%20the%20demand%20for%20care%20grows.%20But%20the%20lure%20of%20the%20CMO%20role%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20exacerbating%20the%20shortage%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20that's%20the%20hope%20among%20the%20CMOs%20I%20spoke%20to.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it's%20a%20zero-sum%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Maytal.%20Many%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F22-most-promising-healthcare-ai-startups-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%20health%20tech%20startups%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20aimed%20at%20shortening%20wait%20times%20in%20hospitals%20and%20clinics%20or%20bringing%20primary%20care%20to%20underserved%20regions%20and%20underserved%20groups%20who%20are%20more%20prone%20to%20end%20up%20in%20emergency%20rooms%20with%20illnesses%20that%20could%20have%20been%20treated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Shah%2C%20Dr.%20Nate%20Favini%2C%20who%20started%20as%20his%20company's%20first%20CMO%20last%20year%2C%20sees%20his%20role%20as%20%26quot%3Bdoctoring%20at%20a%20larger%20scale.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%2C%20Pair%20Team%2C%20is%20a%20San%20Francisco-based%20digital%20health%20startup%20that%20uses%20AI%20to%20connect%20Medicaid%20patients%20to%20care.%20After%20watching%20his%20dad%20work%20in%20emergency%20medicine%20in%20rural%20Pennsylvania%2C%20he%20entered%20the%20field%20%26quot%3Bknowing%20the%20healthcare%20system%20was%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20knew%20I%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20higher-level%20impact%20on%20the%20system.%26quot%3B%20When%20he%20made%20the%20transition%20to%20health%20tech%20from%20caring%20for%20primarily%20Medicare%20patients%2C%20some%20colleagues%20thought%20he%20was%20crazy%20or%20selling%20out%2C%20he%20says.%20Now%2C%20more%20are%20coming%20around.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20massive%20opportunity%20to%20harness%20technology%20to%20deliver%20better%20care%20at%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost%20and%20get%20really%20good%20care%20to%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20Favini%20tells%20me.%20I