olicymakers%20are%20sounding%20the%20alarm%20about%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20promise%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-deportation-plans-increase-retirement-costs-healthcare-immigration-social-security-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeport%20millions%20of%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20those%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20do%20not%20have%20Social%20Security%20numbers%2C%20the%20IRS%20issues%20individual%20taxpayer%20identification%20numbers%20(ITINs)%2C%20which%20help%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethem%20to%20pay%20taxes.%20The%20main%20reason%20it's%20beneficial%20for%20them%20to%20do%20so%20is%20that%20a%20history%20of%20tax%20payments%20can%20help%20them%20along%20the%20path%20to%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20ITINs%20don't%20provide%20legal%20immigration%20status%2C%20work%20authorization%2C%20or%20access%20to%20federal%20benefit%20programs%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicare.%20Many%20people%20working%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20adhere%20to%20IRS%20requirements%20because%20noncompliance%20can%20put%20them%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20deportation%20for%20themselves%20or%20family%20members%2C%20said%20Cecilia%20Menj%C3%ADvar%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Los%20Angeles%20who%20specializes%20in%20immigration%20policy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.americanimmigrationcouncil.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fresearch%2Fthe_facts_about_the_individual_tax_identification_number_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPaying%20taxes%20with%20ITINs%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20also%20help%20immigrants%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20build%20a%20work%20history%20and%20show%20strong%20moral%20character%2C%20which%20could%20help%20them%20later%20in%20any%20immigration%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Social%20Security%20Administration%20previously%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Trump's%20deportation%20plans%20could%20cut%20%2420%20billion%20annually%20in%20lost%20tax%20revenue.%20This%20is%20of%20particular%20concern%20for%20many%20Americans%20as%2C%20in%20roughly%20a%20decade%2C%20Social%20Security%20payments%20could%20shrink%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-benefits-run-out-retirement-crisis-boomers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edwindling%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20revenue%20from%20taxpayers%20with%20ITINs%2C%20the%20Institute%20on%20Taxation%20and%20Economic%20Policy%20estimated%20that%20immigrants%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20paid%20%2496.7%20billion%20in%20US%20taxes%20in%202022.%20More%20than%20half%20went%20to%20the%20federal%20government%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20went%20to%20states%20and%20localities.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20this%20tax%20revenue%20also%20went%20toward%20welfare%20programs%20like%20SNAP%2C%20Supplemental%20Security%20Income%2C%20unemployment%2C%20housing%20assistance%2C%20and%20various%20tax%20credits%2C%20for%20which%20immigrants%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%20don't%20qualify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227cc574fa-f1c5-43f4-a165-53a17b4ab78b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20role%20of%20the%20immigrant%20workforce%20in%20US%20tax%20revenue%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy-us-birth-rate-declining-population-immigration-china-elon-musk-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20birth%20rate%20is%20declining%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20number%20of%20retirees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-social-security-works-medicare-food-stamps-retirement-elder-poverty-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclaiming%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20ballooning%2C%20meaning%20immigrants%20are%20a%20significant%20piece%20of%20US%20workforce%20growth%20and%20keeping%20state%20and%20federal%20coffers%20full.%20As%20of%20July%202023%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20data%20available%2C%20there%20were%20over%2011%20million%20immigrants%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%2C%20per%20the%20Center%20for%20Migration%20Studies.%20More%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcmsny.org%2Fimportance-of-immigrant-labor-to-us-economy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20those%20individuals%20are%20actively%20in%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20tax%20system's%20emphasis%20on%20immigrant%20contributions%20isn't%20new.%20The%20ITIN%20system%20was%20created%20in%20the%201990s%20to%20allow%20foreign%20nationals%20to%20comply%20with%20tax%20law.%20Some%20ITIN-holders%20are%20living%20in%20the%20US%20illegally%2C%20others%20are%20student%20visa%20holders%2C%20spouses%20and%20children%20of%20those%20with%20employment%20visas%2C%20or%20survivors%20of%20domestic%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20immigrant%20taxpayers%20have%20an%20ITIN%2C%20the%20IRS%20can't%20share%20ITIN%20information%20with%20other%20government%20agencies%2C%20and%20the%20identification%20numbers%20cannot%20be%20used%20by%20employers%20or%20the%20government%20to%20assess%20whether%20someone%20is%20undocumented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20ITIN%20can%20be%20used%20to%20retroactively%20count%20toward%20a%20person's%20Social%20Security%20benefit%20amount%20if%20they%20later%20become%20a%20citizen%2C%20per%20the%20American%20Immigration%20Council.%20People%20can%20also%20use%20the%20number%20to%20open%20a%20bank%20account%20or%20obtain%20a%20driver's%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20immigrants%20do%20not%20automatically%20gain%20access%20to%20retirement%20or%20welfare%20benefits%20once%20they%20obtain%20citizenship.%20A%201996%20law%20prevents%20immigrants%20who%20become%20citizens%20from%20accessing%20certain%20aid%20for%20five%20years%20after%20receiving%20documentation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMenj%C3%ADvar%20said%20immigrants%20%E2%80%94%20regardless%20of%20their%20citizenship%20status%20%E2%80%94%20consistently%20contribute%20more%20to%20taxes%20than%20they%20receive%20in%20benefits.%20As%20Trump%20continues%20to%20carry%20out%20his%20mass%20deportation%20plan%2C%20she%20expects%20the%20impact%20on%20immigrant%20workers%20will%20%26quot%3Breverberate%26quot%3B%20across%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20remove%20several%20million%20people%20from%20contributing%20taxes%20and%20supporting%20local%20economies%20where%20they%20live%20through%20sales%20taxes%20and%20property%20taxes%2C%20it's%20all%20going%20to%20be%20affected%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fundocumented-immigrants-pay-taxes-dont-receive-social-security-medicare-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738832462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a375437bb3f854015bc9d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fundocumented-immigrants-pay-taxes-dont-receive-social-security-medicare-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Immigrants%20are%20vital%20to%20US%20tax%20revenue%20amid%20a%20declining%20birth%20rate%20and%20rising%20number%20of%20retirees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fundocumented-immigrants-pay-taxes-dont-receive-social-security-medicare-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'History%20takes%20its%20revenge'%3A%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20response%20after%20mob%20vandalises%20father's%20Mujibur%20Rahman's%20house%20in%20Dhaka%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738832330000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117977391%2Cimgsize-1473076.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%